  "prompt": "Why does Telegram have two different macOS apps?",
  "response": "Telegram offers two different macOS apps to cater to different user preferences and needs:\n\n1. **Telegram Desktop (macOS App Store Version)**:\n   - This version is available on the macOS App Store, making it easy for users to download and update directly through Apple's platform.\n   - It adheres to Apple's App Store guidelines, which may include restrictions on certain features or functionalities.\n   - Users who prefer the convenience of the App Store and automatic updates often opt for this version.\n\n2. **Telegram Desktop (Direct Download Version)**:\n   - This version can be downloaded directly from Telegram's official website.\n   - It is frequently updated with the latest features and improvements, often ahead of the App Store version.\n   - It offers more flexibility and may include features that are not available in the App Store version due to Apple's restrictions.\n   - Users who want the most up-to-date version or need access to specific features not available in the App Store version prefer this option.\n\nThe dual availability ensures that Telegram can reach a broader audience while accommodating different preferences for app distribution and updates.",
